reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 16, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great simple desk lamp with nice features. Worth it!
reviews.reviewText: I gotta say I am really loving this lamp. It's bright, and if you need to you can adjust the brightness to better suit your eyes. It's got a sundown color setting for night time so it doesn't strain your eyes. It's kind of like the blue filter setting many computers and phones are adding that add a slightly orange filter to the screen. The lamp however uses what I would call tan LED's. They're not orange and they're not brown, they're TAN! Jokes aside it's a great feature for someone like me who is constantly reading and using my computer to study. The other great feature is this lamp has two standard wall outlets so it acts like an extension cord as well. I didn't check the rating but I'd only use it for a laptop charger or something else lightweight. On top of all that it has 3 USB ports, two which put out 1 amp at 5volts and one that puts out 2 amps at 5 volts, so you can charge multiple devices at a time or if you need more light you can buy some USB lamps, or maybe even a USB fan and just plug em into your lamp. Now the chargers are not controlled by the lamp, they're always on basically. Though they don't draw their full power unless they're charging. You can tell because the base only gets warm when it's been charging something which is what happens when transformers consume power because nothing is 100% efficient and some heat gets lost in the process.My only real qualm with this thing is how light the base is. It's not a big issue, but I wish I could put a lead weight in it just to give it more heft. Also if they moved the lamp neck closer to the middle or extended the base a little farther behind the lamp neck so you could open it one handed that'd be even better. Again not a big issue, it's a great little lamp and I'd still recommend it if you want something simple and you have a lot of electronics and accessories to keep charged like I do.
